- Which prior issues are PARTIALLY ADDRESSED?
Include this assessment in your rejection reason if rejecting.
{{- end}}

REVIEW PHASE:
1. Early drift check: git -C {{.WorktreePath}} rev-parse HEAD — if it doesn't match REVIEW_COMMIT ({{.ReviewCommit}}), stop early (verdict submission will reject the mismatch).
2. Read the epic-writing skill: ~/.liza/skills/epic-writing/SKILL.md
3. Inspect worktree changes: git -C {{.WorktreePath}} diff {{.BaseCommit}}..{{.ReviewCommit}}
4. Validate done_when criteria are satisfied.
5. Verify output[] entries: run liza_get with {"query": "tasks/{{.Task.ID}}"} and confirm
   output[] has one entry per capability with valid desc, done_when, scope, spec_ref.
6. Check each proposed capability against the review checklist and anti-pattern table above.
7. Submit verdict with liza_submit_verdict.

